        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 17 at 7:23PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 722 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Redding, or near Danbury, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bridgeport, Norwalk, Danbury, Shelton, New Canaan, Newtown,
Fairfield, Trumbull, Westport, Ridgefield, Monroe, Bethel, Wilton,
Weston, and Redding.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
